{
  "texts": [
    "This provides indispensable theoretical guidance for researchers to break through current quality bottlenecks and for practitioners to build industrialgrade testing tools.",
    "ConclusionAdopting a systems engineering perspective, this paper presents a systematic review of the field of LLM-based unit test generation.",
    "Through an in-depth analysis of 115 studies, we not only reveal the dominance of prompt engineering strategies (89%) but also construct a unified analytical framework covering \"pre-generation context enrichment, \" \"post-generation quality assurance, \" and \"system-level synergy. \"",
    "This framework elucidates how classic software engineering methods are repurposed to compensate for the inherent deficiencies of LLMs in semantic understanding and output stability.Our analysis indicates that the field is currently at a critical transition period from \"single-point generation\" to \"system-level synergy. \"",
    "Current challenges, such as the low usability of generated code and the lack of accuracy in test oracles, point to the future evolutionary path of building hybrid intelligent systems that deeply integrate traditional automation technologies, as well as testing agents with autonomous perception and decision-making capabilities."
  ]
}